Package services

Class EmotionService

java.lang.Object
services.EmotionService
public class EmotionService extends Object

This class contains the method to get the data insert by the user, the method to manipulate the data, and the method to call the factory.

Author:
Diana Cantaluppi, Matr. 744457 Sede Como., Edoardo Ballabio, Matr. 745115 Sede Como.

      public EmotionFelt insertEmotionData(Scanner cmdInput, boolean newEmotion, Long songId, Map<String,EmotionFelt> emotionByUserAndSong)
      This method allows you to insert a new emotion felt by the user with the associated data. If the emotion felt by the user already exists, it is possible to update the associated data.

      newEmotion - A Boolean to check if the emotion is new or already exists.
